<h1>Murudeshwara – Temple Town & Diving Hub</h1>
<p>Murudeshwara is a stunning coastal destination and spiritual magnet, famous for its 123‑ft Shiva statue on Kanduka Hill—one of the world’s tallest—with the 20‑story Raja Gopura tower offering breathtaking Arabian Sea views :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}.</p>

<h1>Legend & Architecture</h1>
<p>The temple marks the mythical resting place of the Atma Linga, linked to Ravana and Ganesha’s lore during the Ramayana era :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}. Its modern Dravidian design and elevator-access tower are built alongside ancient sanctums housing the Shiva Linga :contentReference[oaicite:10]{index=10}.</p>


<h1>Festivals, Rituals & Best Time to Visit</h1>
<p>Murudeshwara comes alive during Maha Shivaratri, Kartika Deepam, Rathotsava, and daily abhishekams—celebrated beneath the iconic gopura and statue fountainlight :contentReference[oaicite:14]{index=14}.</p>
<p>Ideal visiting season is **October to March**—pleasant weather, active spiritual ceremonies, and optimal conditions for diving and beach activities :contentReference[oaicite:15]{index=15}.</p>

<h1>Visitor Planning & Infrastructure</h1>
<p>Access is via Mangalore Airport (≈153 km), direct rail service (Murudeshwara Station, ~2 km away), and smooth NH‑66 coastal highway connectivity :contentReference[oaicite:16]{index=16}. Accommodations range from homestays and lodges to beachfront resorts like RNS Residency :contentReference[oaicite:17]{index=17}.</p>


